Alembic migrations for Travel AI (TAI).

env.py reads DATABASE_URL from api.config.Settings and builds the async engine
via api.db.build_engine, so migrations target the same DB the app uses (with the
same async-driver selection and hosted-Postgres DSN normalization). alembic.ini's
sqlalchemy.url is intentionally unset.

Common commands (run from the repo root, with the venv active):

    alembic upgrade head                      # apply all migrations
    alembic revision --autogenerate -m "..."  # create a migration from model changes
    alembic check                             # fail if models have drifted from head

On deploy, Postgres is migrated automatically: the app lifespan runs
`alembic upgrade head` when DATABASE_URL points at Postgres. SQLite/dev keeps the
zero-config Base.metadata.create_all path.
